(10) (10) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
(a) "Broadband internet access service" means a mass-market retail service by wire or radio that
provides the capability to transmit data to and receive data from all or substantially all internet endpoints. The
term includes capabilities that are incidental to and enable the operation of the communications service. The
term does not include dial-up internet access service.
